{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c8f5023-9996-4bac-a542-e7669464c6fd","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # confirm 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # verify it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso check your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references should be updated to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"60ba871a-f1b0-4348-8a54-003cf1faef90","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore since the working directory is empty and not a git repo.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"7028:F29A5:8DF6EF:A3F58F:69FBEE48"},"id":"8ba8b433-50d7-49bf-811d-42f27c55db53","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:43:44.880Z","parentId":"456efdc5-4c9b-438c-a7ff-7b88083062ed"}
